{
  "texts": [
    "When it is not possible to derive such estimates beforehand, we suggest that researchers conduct pilot studies in order to gain a more concrete sense of what can potentially be gained.",
    "For another, harmonizing data can allow researchers to assess the generalizability or transportability of a given finding 85, 86.",
    "Note that while the two terms are closely related, generalizability refers to whether causal effects can travel from the sample to the population under question (e.g.",
    "from a survey of students in a given school to all students in the school) while transportability refers to whether causal effects can travel to (at least partly) external populations (e.g.",
    "from a survey of students in a given school to students in other schools) 87."
  ]
}